This is an applet that allows a user to interact with and learn basic AI
classifiers for linear regressors and perceptron. The user will be able to
spawn data points on mouse clicks and choose their labels. From these spawned
data points, the user can see the linear and perceptron classifiers. The code
for the software is found in code for development purposes. The installer is
found in installer and works relative to heiarchy found in this directory. To
install, simply run the install script. The uninstall script will remove this
software if you have already installed it. Installing the software add the
code and executor script to run the code in /usr/bin. It will create a folder
called Classifier and put the code there. The executor will be a file called
classifer which you just need to type in the command line. You might need to
use sudo to run this software.
